Additional interoperability notice
----------------------------------

Shortpy IDE is an independent implementation and integration layer for editing
Shortcuts-oriented Python in Visual Studio Code and for communicating with
locally installed Apple Shortcuts and iOS Simulator runtime components.

This repository licenses only the original code, scripts, extension glue,
bridge implementation, documentation, and other materials contained in this
repository, except for third-party portions identified in `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md`.
It does not include, license, sublicense, or grant any rights in Apple software,
Apple private frameworks, Xcode, iOS Simulator runtimes, macOS Shortcuts,
Visual Studio Code, Microsoft software, or any other third-party software,
services, APIs, SDKs, or trademarks.

Shortpy IDE is not affiliated with, endorsed by, sponsored by, or approved by
Apple Inc. or Microsoft Corporation. Apple, Shortcuts, macOS, iOS, Xcode, Siri,
Visual Studio Code, VS Code, and related names or marks are trademarks of their
respective owners.

The Software may interoperate with locally installed Apple software and private
or undocumented runtime behavior. No representation or warranty is made that
the Software will function with any current or future version of Apple software,
Visual Studio Code, simulator runtimes, signing tools, shortcut files, or
related services. Users are responsible for ensuring that their use of this
Software complies with all applicable laws and third-party license terms.
